    Create seroprevalence table

    sero_table.Rd

    Create seroprevalence table

    Usage

    sero_table(df, pathogen)

    Arguments

    df

    processed data with parameter information produced by data_param_table()

    pathogen

    name of pathogen

    Value

    returns flextable with a summary of seroprevalence data

    Examples

    df <- data_param_table(pathogen = "marburg", exclude = c(15, 17))
#> Rows: 70 Columns: 52
